@7441 = ~Critical hit chances increased by Whispers of Silence~

@7450 = ~The Cloak of Displacement is a magical item that causes subtle shifts in the image of its wearer. It has the power to actually shift an individual's image by as much as six inches in any direction from their actual location. Aside from being an effective defense in combat situations, it has also been the cause of serious eyestrain amongst fellow party members.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +4 vs. missile attacks
– Damage resistance: +5%
– Saves vs. Death, Breath, and Wand: +2

Weight: 3~

@7480 = ~The mad necromancer and lich N'Ashtar Nikadeemus forged this helmet from the bones of his own parents. His highest ranked general would wear it when he rode into battle, using it to instantly slay the commanders of the opposing army. After that, the skeletal armies of N'Ashtar would overrun their demoralized enemies. When N'Ashtar finally fell, the Skull of Death was supposedly destroyed.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Protects against critical hits
– Saves vs. Necromancy: +4
– Immunity to necromantic instant-death magic, and vorpal effects

Charge abilities:
– Death Spell once per day
  Slays creatures with fewer than 9 Hit Dice
  Range: 50 ft.
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius

– Finger of Death once per day
  Slays target if Save vs. Spell at -2 is failed
  Range: 30 ft.
  Area of effect: One target

Weight: 2~

@7610 = ~These gem-studded leather gloves are enchanted so as to augment the skills of any Bard, no matter the kind.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Different bards get different bonuses:
  All bards: +2 Armor Class, THAC0, Damage, and casting speed. +1 memorizable spells from level 1 to 6
  Skalds: +1 bonus to Strength and +1/2 attacks per round
  Blades: +1 bonus to Dexterity and +1/2 attacks per round
  Jesters: Immune to confusion, slow, and unconsciousness. +6 bonus to saves vs. Enchantment effects

Weight: 1~

@7611 = ~Bards~

@7650 = ~Boots of Avoidance: Senses of the Cat
The magic of these boots was specifically designed to detect incoming attacks and aid the wearer in avoiding them. They were originally commissioned by the instructor of an archery academy who had tired of suffering "accidents" at the hands of his inexperienced students.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +1 Armor Class, +4 extra vs. missile attacks
– Saves vs. Breath: +1
– Movement rate increased by a factor of 3

Weight: 4~

@7740 = ~Kazgaroth was an aspect of Bhaal who was a powerful, intelligent, shapeshifting evil beast opposed to the balance and the influence of the Earthmother on the Moonshae Isles. This horn is thought to be made from one its tusks. When blown upon, no sound issues from the horn. Instead, the user of the horn is encased in a globe of power for a short duration. The bubble greatly increases the user's magical defenses and saving throws, as well as partially deflecting incoming physical attacks. The horn draws from the life force of the user every time it is used.

STATISTICS:

Charge abilities:
Three times per day, blow the horn to activate the powers:
  – Immunity to 1st, 2nd, and 3rd-level spells
  – Armor Class: +2, +6 vs. missile attacks
  – Saving Throws: +2
  – Magic Resistance: +10%
  – Physical Resistance: +8%
  – Duration: 5 rounds
  – Kazgaroth's Offering: the user has a 50% chance of suffering a random penalty for 2 turns after use.

Weight: 1~

@7741 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -10 Max Hit Points~
@7742 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -3 THAC0~
@7743 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -2 Damage~
@7744 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -2 Strength~
@7745 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -2 Constitution~
@7746 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -2 Dexterity~
@7747 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -1 Saving Throws~
@7748 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: +2 Casting Speed~
@7749 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -4 Saves vs. Death~
@7750 = ~Kazgaroth's Offering: -50% movement speed~

@7820 = ~This ring, designed for the hero Zachiira, is engraved with holy symbols. When Zachiira requested aid from King Strohm III, it was the king’s royal advisor, the great and powerful Theurgist Karlash Arnostognas, who made this item, in the hope that it would aid the hero in her battle against a demon vampire. Zachiira survived the encounter, but sadly her triumphal return was met with rather less celebration and rather more grief, as the good king was already dead when she arrived. Zachiira laid the holy artifact at the entrance to the king’s tomb, and it was there the relic was discovered by wandering thrill-seekers.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +2 vs. evil creatures
– Attack damage and THAC0: +1 vs. evil creatures
– Hit Points: +10
– Chant
– One extra divine spell slot for level 1 and 2 (good-aligned only)

Weight: 0~

@7830 = ~Two small round topazes flank the symbol of Caelar Argent engraved on this ring's silver band. Such rings testify to the high status of crusaders who have shown their prowess in battle or in some way demonstrated unwavering commitment to the Shining Lady's cause.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +1, +3 vs. demons and devils
– Saving Throws: +1, +3 vs. demons and devils
– Attack damage and THAC0: +2 vs. demons and devils

Weight: 0~

@7840 = ~Constructed from a rhino beetle's sturdy shell, this armor offers its wearer excellent protection without impeding their motion to the same extent as traditional metal plate mail. The unusual material makes this suit of armor particularly effective against all but crushing weapons.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Missile Damage Resistance: +18%
– Slashing Damage Resistance: +12%
– Piercing Damage Resistance: +8%

Armor Class: 1 (-2 vs. missile, -1 vs. slashing, 0 vs. piercing)
Requires:
 8 Strength

Weight: 25~

@7850 = ~The rhino beetle's carapace makes a most effective shield provided one can survive long enough to pry a piece off the creature. Lightweight but sturdy, this item makes a powerful argument for the premise that the best shields are found in nature, not the forge. The unusual material makes the shield particularly effective against all but crushing weapons.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +3, an extra +2 vs. missile attacks, and +1 vs. slashing attacks
– Missile Damage Resistance: +12%
– Slashing Damage resistance: +8%
– Piercing Damage Resistance: +5%

Requires:
 10 Strength

Weight: 6~

@7860 = ~This shield was carried by a mercenary working with the Order of the Steel Fang. The warriors of the order were impressed with the mercenary's tenacity and courage. She charged into battle without hesitation and seemed to fight all the harder when she was wounded. When their quest was completed, the Order of the Steel Fang gifted a battleaxe to the mercenary as thanks for her service. In turn, she gave the order her shield as a sign of respect. The shield stayed in the order for years until it was lost on a battlefield.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Armor Class: +3, an extra +1 vs. missile attacks
– Fire Resistance: +25%

Combat abilities:
– When the wielder's Hit Points drop below 50%, <PRO_HESHE> gains +2 Strength for 5 rounds and may not die from any physical injury for 1 round. The Strength benefit does not stack, and the latter effect can only trigger once every turn.

Requires:
 10 Strength

Weight: 4~

@8030 = ~Created for the Grandmaster Assassin Vita Muerte, this suit not only provided protection but also enabled Vita to better pursue and kill her fleeing victims... as the unfortunate wizard who fashioned this item for the ruthless killer soon learned.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
– Doubles movement rate
– Critical misses are no longer possible (thieves only)

Different kinds of benefits for backstabs are unlocked depending on the rogue wearing this suit:
  – Cripple: Slows the target for 1 round and reduces Strength, Dexterity, and casting speed by 4 for 4 rounds if the target fails a Save vs. Death (kitless thieves).
  – Subdue: Knocks the target unconscious for 4 rounds if they fail a Save vs. Death. Additionally, inflicts 10 points of non-lethal damage. However, any further damage will wake the target (Bounty Hunter and Stalker).
  – Beshadow: Harnesses shadow magic to enhance self-defense and offense. Grants 5% damage resistance for 2 rounds, with a 20% chance to become invisible for 2 rounds. During this time, damage increases by 2 and critical hit chances improve by 5% (Shadowdancer). These effects do not stack.
  – Death Attack: Strikes the target with a lethal precision. If the target fails a Save vs. Death, they are stunned for 1 round. After the stun wears off, if the target has 60 Hit Points or less, they must make another Save vs. Death or die instantly. If the second save is successful, the target instead suffers 2d6 poison damage and becomes more vulnerable to subsequent Death Attacks, receiving a -4 penalty to Saves vs. Death for 5 rounds (Assassin).

Charge abilities:
– Expose Weakness once per day
  Special: Removes the target's immunity to backstabs (if applicable), increases damage taken from piercing and slashing attacks by 10%, and imposes a -4 penalty to Armor Class specifically against those attack types.
  Duration: 4 rounds

Armor Class: 1 (-1 vs. slashing, 0 vs. piercing and missile)
Requires:
 6 Strength

Weight: 5~

